org.apache.poi.xwpf.usermodel

Enum BreakType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BreakType>
      • org.apache.poi.xwpf.usermodel.BreakType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BreakType> 

    public enum BreakType
extends java.lang.Enum<BreakType>
    Specifies the possible types of break characters in a WordprocessingML document. The break type determines the next location where text shall be placed after this manual break is applied to the text contents(指定WordcastingML文档中可能出现的标点符号类型。中断类型确定将此手动中断应用于文本内容后文本应放置的下一个位置)
    Author:
    Gisella Bronzetti

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      COLUMN
      Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next column available on the current page when the document is displayed in page view.(指定当文档在页面视图中显示时，当前中断应在当前页面上可用的下一列上自行重新启动。)
      PAGE
      Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next page of the document when the document is displayed in page view.(指定当文档在页面视图中显示时，当前中断应在文档的下一页上自行重新启动。)
      TEXT_WRAPPING
      Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next line in the document when the document is displayed in page view.(指定在页面视图中显示文档时，当前分隔符应在文档的下一行重新开始。)

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PAGE

        public static final BreakType PAGE
        Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next page of the document when the document is displayed in page view.(指定当文档在页面视图中显示时，当前中断应在文档的下一页上自行重新启动。)

      • COLUMN

        public static final BreakType COLUMN
        Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next column available on the current page when the document is displayed in page view.

        If the current section is not divided into columns, or the column break occurs in the last column on the current page when displayed, then the restart location for text shall be the next page in the document.

        (指定当文档在页面视图中显示时，当前中断应在当前页面上可用的下一列上自行重新启动。如果当前部分未分为列，或者显示时当前页面的最后一列出现分栏，则文本的重新启动位置应为文档中的下一页。)

      • TEXT_WRAPPING

        public static final BreakType TEXT_WRAPPING
        Specifies that the current break shall restart itself on the next line in the document when the document is displayed in page view. The determine of the next line shall be done subject to the value of the clear attribute on the specified break character.(指定在页面视图中显示文档时，当前分隔符应在文档的下一行重新开始。下一行的确定应根据指定中断字符上clear属性的值来确定。)
